-- Nigeria Planning to Offer a $500 Million Eurobond by October, ThisDay Says
-- Alastair Reed
-- 2010-06-30T05:58:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/nigeria-planning-to-offer-a-500-million-eurobond-by-october-thisday-says.html

          
          
             Nigeria will sell $500 million of
Eurobonds by the end of October,  ThisDay reported , citing
 Abraham Nwankwo , director general of the Debt Management Office.  
 The Eurobond issue is part of a plan to manage Nigeria’s
debt, ThisDay said. The West African nation’s debt is 13.98
percent of gross domestic product, Finance Minister  Olusegun Aganga  said on May 5.  
